---
title: Panko Parm Poulet with Potatoes over Baby Spinach in a Creamy Lemon Dressing
description: The words “chicken parm” usually have us reaching for our stretchy pants, but this version has all of the cheesy, breaded goodness you know and love in a less over-the-top package. The chicken breasts are baked, not fried, while the heavy sauce is swapped out for a spinach salad with a fresh-squeezed creamy lemon dressing.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/15-01-7aa8ddb8.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/15-01-2263ddc9.pdf
cuisine: North America
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 540 kcal
  fat: 20 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 43 g
  sugar: 5 g
  protein: 52 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 420 mg
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/panko-parm-poulet-with-potatoes-58af23eac9fd080f2d1aa0e3
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ¾-inch cubes. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast in oven until lightly browned and tender, about ~{25%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Meanwhile, combine @Panko Breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, @Parmesan Cheese{¼%cup}, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} in a #small bowl{}.

Place @chicken breasts{2%pieces} between two pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #rolling pin{}, #mallet{}, or #heavy-bottomed pan{} until ½ inch thick. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Repeat with remaining chicken breast.

Place chicken breasts on a lightly oiled baking sheet and brush tops with 2 TBSP @Sour Cream{3%tablespoon} (we'll be using more later). Press panko mixture into sour cream. Bake in oven until chicken is cooked through and crust is crispy, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Halve @lemon{1%unit}. Cut one half into wedges. In a #large bowl{}, combine 1 TBSP sour cream (you'll have some left over), a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. When potatoes are done, add to bowl along with @Spinach{5%ounce} and toss to coat evenly. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Divide salad between plates and top with chicken. Serve with lemon wedges on the side for squeezing over.